16/06/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- In his yearly report before the OSCE Permanent Council in Vienna on Thursday (15 June), OSCE mission to Croatia head Jorge Fuentes applauded the enormous progress in reform the country has achieved.
Fuentes said that Croatia has made the most headway in democratisation of all the OSCE mission countries.
He also said the present level of co-operation between Croatia and OSCE was excellent, and urged more efforts for refugee return and judicial reform.
(Vecernji List - 16/06/06;
Hina - 15/06/06)
